author: Laurence Norman
title: EU’s Chief Negotiator Throws Doubt on Hopes for Quick Brexit Deal
text:
BRUSSELS—Fresh tension between the European Union and the U.K on Brexit talks is threatening to delay progress on any agreement over a transition period, sending sterling to a three-week low Friday.
The EU’s chief negotiator, Michel Barnier, warned Friday that friction between London and Brussels over the U.K.’s rights and obligations during a proposed two-year transition period could hold up an agreement on the adjustment period.
